public DataGroup getDataGroup(int dataGroupFilePos)
                       throws java.io.IOException,
                              java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                              UnsignedOutOfLimitsException
Returns a DataGroup object based on a DataGroup file position. This is useful when there are many DataGroups and the file position of each DataGroup is known (Calvin CDF). In this case the GenericFileReader::ReadHeader() method should be called with the ReadNoDataGroupHeader flag.
